latestPosts.caption:
Read me⤵️

New era 🍸🦢

She’s back – but not the way you remember her.

2024 cracked me open in ways I never expected.
I moved from the biggest city in my country to the quiet countryside, five hours away from everything I once knew.
I went knees-deep into witchcraft about 1.5 years ago, turned to my goddesses and I never looked back.

Somewhere along the way, I stopped posting. Not because I had nothing to say, but because what I wanted to say didn’t fit the box I’d been placed in.
I’m not here to talk about being a “high value woman” anymore. That narrative suggests some women are worth less than others.
That’s not my truth. We all carry sacred value in our own way.

My taste in men changed, give me the tattooed, jacked, emotionally complex ones now. Y’all can keep the clean-cut nepo babies. (Respectfully)
And no, I won’t be handing out dating advice anymore. That chapter is closed.

I’m still feminine. Still traditional in many ways. But I’m not your textbook classy woman and I have no desire to be.
I’ve been judged, ridiculed, and told to repent more times than I can count. But I’ll tell you this: for every “Jesus saves” comment, I light a candle to Mother Hekate, Mother Lilith and Lady Aphrodite instead.

I know I’ve lost followers. I know I’ll lose more.
And you know what? I’m good with that.
I’m here for the women who stay.

So what can you expect from me now?

fashion content
countryside moments
witchy + spiritual stories only
honest glimpses into my life: law school, horses, spellwork & all the magic in between

What you won’t find here anymore:

dating tips
high value woman content

This space is sacred now.
And if you’re still here… I see you. I appreciate you. And we’re just getting started.

(Picture edited w FaceApp and FaceTune. Don’t compare yourself to people online!🤍)
